## Component Variants

### Button Variants
- Primary: Solid blue
- Secondary: Outlined blue
- Success: Solid green
- Danger: Solid red
- Ghost: Transparent
- Sizes: Small (32px), Medium (40px), Large (48px)

### Card Variants
- Default: White background
- Bordered: White with border
- Elevated: With shadow
- Flat: No shadow

### Input Variants
- Default: Standard input
- Search: With search icon
- Password: With show/hide toggle
- Textarea: Multi-line
- Error: Red border and message

## Auto Layout Patterns

### Button Groups
- Horizontal stack
- 8px gap between buttons
- Equal width or auto width

### Form Fields
- Vertical stack
- 16px gap between fields
- Label above input
- 8px gap between label and input

### Card Grids
- Responsive grid
- Min width 320px
- Auto fit columns
- 24px gap

### Navigation Lists
- Vertical stack
- 8px gap
- Icon + text alignment
- Hover states

## Responsive Behavior

### Mobile Adaptations
- Single column layout
- Stacked navigation
- Full width buttons
- Touch-friendly sizing (44px minimum)
- Simplified content

### Tablet Adaptations
- 2-column grid for cards
- Condensed sidebars
- Medium-sized touch targets

### Desktop Optimizations
- Multi-column layouts
- Hover states
- Keyboard navigation
- Expanded content

## Accessibility Guidelines

### Color Contrast
- Text on background: 4.5:1 minimum
- Large text: 3:1 minimum
- Interactive elements: 3:1 minimum

### Focus Indicators
- 2px solid Primary Blue
- 2px border radius
- Visible on keyboard navigation

### Semantic Structure
- Proper heading hierarchy
- ARIA labels where needed
- Screen reader friendly

## Implementation Notes

### Component Naming Convention
- Component/Type/Variant/Size
- Example: Button/Primary/Default/Medium

### Layer Organization
- Components at top level
- Variants as nested components
- Assets in separate frames

### Version Control
- Use Figma's version history
- Document changes in descriptions
- Tag major updates

This template provides a comprehensive foundation for building the Power Apps permission approval system UI in Figma. Start with the design system setup, then build components systematically following the established patterns.
